modules.description: This module manages ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) operations, including IP-to-MAC address resolution, cache manipulation, and GARP packet transmission. It works with IPv4 addresses (`Ipaddr.V4.t`), MAC addresses (`Macaddr.t`), and Ethernet frames (`Cstruct.t`). Concrete use cases include handling incoming ARP requests and responses, updating local ARP cache entries, and managing IP address bindings on a network interface.

This module handles ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) operations, including parsing and constructing ARP packets, managing ARP tables, and resolving IP addresses to MAC addresses. It works with network interface data structures, IP and MAC address types, and packet buffers. Concrete use cases include network discovery, ARP caching, and responding to ARP requests in network drivers.
